'''''The New Encyclopedia of Snakes''''' is an [[encyclopedia]] by Chris Mattison.

==Book summary==
The encyclopedia has information about snakes that is listed from A-Z. The book has pictures and information about snake [[morphology (biology)|morphology]], [[habitats]], [[diet (nutrition)|diets]], [[hunting]] and defense behaviors, [[Taxonomy (biology)|taxonomy]], and a history of human responses to snakes.<ref>[http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qa3845/is_199901/ai_n8830061 Northeastern Naturalist]</ref>

==Reception==
It was reviewed by ''Science Activities'',<ref>[http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_hb3419/is_199701/ai_n8183482 ''Science Activities'']</ref> ''[[Washington Times]]'',<ref>[http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-7087947/Book-on-snakes-is-unmatched.html ''Washington Times'']</ref> ''[[Booklist]]'', [[King Features Syndicate]], ''Wildlife Activist'', ''Dover Post'', [[Choice (magazine)|''Choice'']], and ''Science Books and Fun''.<ref>[http://press.princeton.edu/quotes/q8481.html Princeton]</ref>

